## When Recall Data Speaks Volumes

317 recalls reported so far this year, 87 of which have been classified as Class I--the highest safety risk category. Moonlight Packing Corporation is a glaring example of a systematic failure: 11 recalls, all Class I. That's not just bad luck, that's bad management. 

## Breakdown of Recent Failures

Recent recalls include improperly labeled products, undeclared allergens, and even undeclared pharmaceutical substances. Moonlight Packing Corporation is not alone, however: Albertsons Companies LLC and Made Fresh Salads Inc also feature prominently in the recall statistics.

## What Does This Mean?

A pattern of repeated safety violations among these brands suggests serious underlying issues. With recall counts growing monthly, it's time for the industry to take a hard look at why these situations keep recurring.

## Recommendations to Consumers

When shopping for products, be vigilant. Checking labels and recall announcements can help mitigate risks in your pantry.
